distinfo.techpreq: To use this data requires software that supports ArcView® GIS shapefiles.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the features from ArcWorld 1:25M. Added and replaced features from ArcWorld 1:3M. Generalized to match detail of the Cntry00.shp. Added attribute values from the Rand McNally New International Atlas, the Times Atlas of the World, and the Digital Chart of the World. Updated Area attribute. Removed unneeded attributes. Renamed an attribute. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was extracted from the ArcWorld 1:25M and 1:3M databases and then generalized (tolerance unknown). The positional accuracy is unknown.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is exported using Avenue request ExportClean. This request verifies and enforces the correctness of shapes.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
